{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 43511368, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "SOCPL-2021-SOC-DIALOG-01", "title": "Support for social dialogue", "publicationDateLong": 1619481600000, "callIdentifier": "SOCPL-2021-SOC-DIALOG", "callTitle": "Support for social dialogue", "callccm2Id": 43511373, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "workProgrammepart": {"id": 288551, "ccm_id": 43516836, "wp_part": "SOCPL-2021", "wp_year": "SOCPL-2021", "wp_title": "SOCPL-2021", "wp_website": "https://ec.europa.eu/european-social-fund-plus/en/esf-direct-easi", "wp_document": "https://ec.europa.eu/social/main.jsp?advSearchKey=prerogatives"}, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43252517, "abbreviation": "SOCPL", "description": "Social Prerogative and Specific Competencies Lines (SOCPL)"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43252542, "abbreviation": "SOCPL-1-1", "description": "SOCPL-1-1"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "SOCPL-PJG SOCPL Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43251093, "abbreviation": "SOCPL-AG", "description": "SOCPL Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "27 April 2021", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["30 June 2021"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3310056": [{"action": "SOCPL-2021-SOC-DIALOG-01 - SOCPL-PJG SOCPL Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "27 April 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["30 June 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 15370000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2021"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">ExpectedOutcome</SPAN>:<p>This call aims at contributing to the promotion of social dialogue at cross-industry and sectoral level, developing European social dialogue, and building and strengthening the capacity of national social partners, in particular following the Covid crisis. </p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p>This call will be used to finance consultations, meetings, negotiations and other actions, as outlined in the European Commission's Communication on <em>The European social dialogue, a force for innovation and change</em> (COM(2002)341), the Communication on <em>Partnership for change in an enlarged Europe \u2013 Enhancing the contribution of European social dialogue</em> (COM(2004)557) and the Commission Staff Working Document on the <em>Functioning and potential of European sectoral social dialogue</em> (SEC(2010)964).</p><p>European social dialogue refers to discussions, consultations, negotiations and joint actions involving organisations representing either side of industry (employers or workers).</p>\n", "conditions": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:-.55pt;line-height:normal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&#10;&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;&#10;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligible countries</span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;&#10;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">:&nbsp;as described in the Call document.</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:&#10;justify;text-indent:-.55pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">EU Member States and in some cases from the European Economic Area (EEA) countries, in accordance with the EEA Agreement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligibility and admissibility conditions:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:&#10;12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"> as described in the Call document.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-style:italic\">Applications must be submitted before the <b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">call deadline </b>and <b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">electronically</b> via the Funding &amp; Tenders Portal Electronic Submission System.</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"> Paper submissions are NOT possible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Text1\" style=\"margin-left:0cm;tab-stops:36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:&#10;12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-style:italic\">Applications (including annexes and supporting documents) must be submitted using the forms provided <i>inside</i> the Submission System.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Body\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:14.0pt\"><span class=\"Hyperlink3\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;&#10;mso-ansi-language:EN-IE\">Applications must be <b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:&#10;normal\">complete</b> and contain:<